The "25-Seat" Sustainable License

Copyright (c) 2026 felvi_games contributors

1. Permitted Free Use

You may use this Software at no cost if you fall into either of these categories:

  Individual: You are a natural person using the software for personal,
  non-commercial projects.

  Small Organization: You are a business, government entity, or non-profit
  with fewer than 25 total users (employees, contractors, or members)
  accessing or benefiting from the Software.

2. The "Stop and Talk" Threshold

Once your organization reaches 25 or more users, your right to use the
Software under this free tier expires.

  Mandatory Agreement: You must contact the Author to negotiate a Commercial
  License or Revenue Share agreement to continue use.

  No Splitting: You may not split a single organization into multiple
  sub-entities to circumvent this user limit.

3. Commercial Hosting / SaaS

Regardless of user count, you may not offer this Software as a managed
service or SaaS to third parties without a separate commercial agreement.
